{\rtf1\ansi \deff0{\fonttbl{\f8\fswiss Arial;}}\margl720\margr2160\pgnstart61\sectd\pgnrestart\pgnstarts61\footery1080{\header \pard\plain\ql MYARC ADVANCED BASIC\par }{\footer \pard\plain\ql \chpgn B    VERSION 4.0  DDI SOFTWARE  \par }\pard \plain\f8\fs20 ECOLOR --Subprogram\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab          ECOLOR\par \par \par \par \par Format\par CALL ECOLOR(color)\par \par Cross reference\par TCOLOR\par \par Description\par CALL ECOLOR(color) is used to "color in" the edge between the text and the border in Graphics modes (2,2), (2,3), (3,2), (3,3).\par \par Example\par CALL ECOLOR(10)\par This would "color in" the edge as Light Red.\par \par Program\par 100 CALL GRAPHICS(3,3)\par 110 CALL TCOLOR(4,14)\par 120 DISPLAY ERASE ALL\par 130 CALL ECOLOR(14)\par RUN\par Line 110 would set the text area for characters as foreground-color of Light Green and background-color to Magenta.\par Line 120 would "paint" the screen with ASCII 32(blank character) in the background-color of Magenta.\par Line 130 would set the edge color to Magenta.\par }
